description.p:
1.


An efficient process for remediation of waste streams, particularly wastewater and groundwater;


2.


Stand-alone compositions for the simultaneous uptake of oil and grease, metals, organics, phosphorus, fluoride, and suspended solids present in waste streams, and particularly industrial waste streams;


3.


A process and compositions that work over a wide pH range, i.e., 2 to 12;


4.


A fast treatment process that can handle flow rates up to 1000 gallons per minute in a continuous setup;


5.


Formation of a dense floc that is fast settling and easy to dewater, resulting in a compact small volume of solid water;


6.


A process that generates solid waste that passes the TCLP test;


7.


Treated water that meets government discharge standards;


8.


Treated water of high quality that can be reused in manufacturing processes; and


9.


A wastewater remediation process which is very economical.
